.TH OPENTERMINALCLI 1 "July 3, 2026" "OpenTerminal" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
openterminalcli \- command line interface for OpenTerminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B openterminalcli
[\fB--json\fR] [\fB--headless\fR] [\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B openterminalcli
controls OpenTerminal from a shell. In attach mode it talks to a running
OpenTerminal GUI or daemon. With
.B --headless
it runs supported local commands in-process without opening the GUI.
.PP
The CLI is local-first. Profile data, settings, notes, layouts, and configured
AI provider secrets are stored on the user's machine. Use
.B --json
for machine-readable output.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B --json
Print compact JSON when the command supports structured output.
.TP
.B --headless
Run the command in an in-process headless runtime.
.TP
.BI --profile " NAME"
Use a named local OpenTerminal profile.
.TP
.B --help
Show help.
.SH CORE COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Show whether the CLI is attached to a GUI/daemon or running headless.
.TP
.B version
Print the CLI version.
.TP
.B doctor [--live-ai]
Diagnose local profile paths, databases, AI provider setup, bundled scripts,
CLI docs/completions, and GUI/daemon attachment status. API keys are never
printed. With
.B --live-ai
it also probes Ollama reachability/model inventory or sends a minimal
OpenAI/Anthropic request through the locally stored key.
.TP
.B security network-audit [--no-sockets]
Audit local MCP server configuration, AI provider endpoints, bridge metadata,
legacy cloud placeholders, and live OpenTerminal-owned sockets. Secrets are
masked; MCP environment values are reported only by key name.
.TP
.B setup [status|profile|ai|doctor]
Local-first onboarding for profile/account and AI provider settings.
.TP
.B sync status
Show the single-owner state for the selected profile. The GUI owns the live
endpoint during interactive work; the daemon owns it for unattended jobs; the
CLI attaches to the active owner or runs one-shot headless commands.
.TP
.B serve [--status|--stop]
Run or manage a headless daemon.
.TP
.B demo trading-system [--symbol BTC] [--crypto-symbol BTC/USD] [--horizon 1h] [--market-prob 50]
Print one read-only proof screen for the local trading stack: daemon/scheduler
state, enabled strategy playlists, live crypto broker reads, local data/model
readiness, horizon signals, and the final TRADE/WATCH/NO TRADE gate. This
command never submits orders.
.TP
.B daemon install|start|stop|restart|status|owner|takeover|release|health|readiness|logs|audit|jobs|monitors|scalp|collectors|notify|ai|paper
Install and manage the per-user macOS LaunchAgent wrapper around
\fBopenterminalcli --profile PROFILE serve\fR, plus local scheduled daemon
jobs for briefs, notebooks, notifications, health checks, and paper strategies.
Only one process owns the interactive profile bridge at a time, but the daemon
can run warm beside a GUI owner. \fBdaemon owner\fR shows the current bridge
owner and scheduler process. \fBdaemon start\fR starts the scheduler as bridge
owner when idle, or as a warm background daemon when the GUI owns the bridge. If
the GUI exits, the warm daemon promotes itself to bridge owner.
\fBdaemon takeover --force --yes\fR deliberately terminates the current GUI owner
and starts/promotes the CLI daemon owner; add \fB--install\fR to write the
LaunchAgent first. \fBdaemon release\fR stops the CLI daemon while leaving the GUI
owner alone.
Daemon jobs support per-job watchdogs with \fB--timeout-sec N\fR, and
\fBdaemon jobs clear-failures [--all|ID_OR_NAME] [--force]\fR acknowledges
reviewed failure history without hiding current failures.
\fBdaemon readiness [--symbol BTC]\fR reports whether live ticks, prediction
market snapshots, horizon models, model-output freshness, and daemon jobs are
safe enough for the local trade gate.
\fBedge publish-horizons [--symbol BTC]\fR publishes timestamped local model
outputs for 5m, 15m, 1h, and daily horizons so daemon readiness can verify
fresh probability snapshots.
\fBedge snapshot-btc5m-live\fR records the current Polymarket BTC 5-minute
market into the local feature store for readiness and audit checks.
\fBedge snapshot-kalshi [--category C] [--family F]\fR records live Kalshi
market snapshots into the same local feature store.
\fBedge journal-evaluate-btc5m-live\fR records a dry-run BTC 5-minute decision
with local features, freshness, probabilities, gate result, and no-trade reason.
\fBedge journal-kalshi-scan\fR records Kalshi dry-run decisions/research-needed
rows from the live scanner. Crypto-family Kalshi rows use the local BTC impulse
anchor by default; pass \fB--no-crypto-anchor\fR to record market-implied-only
research rows.
Inspect it with \fBedge journal list|show|stats|crypto-stats|resolve\fR.
Structured local run history is available with
\fBdaemon jobs history [ID_OR_NAME] [--limit N]\fR,
\fBdaemon jobs failures [ID_OR_NAME]\fR, and
\fBdaemon jobs stats [ID_OR_NAME]\fR.
\fBdaemon collectors repair\fR installs or repairs the managed local feed jobs:
BTC public tick collection, BTC/ETH/SOL scalp gates, crypto scorekeeping,
Kalshi market snapshots, and BTC 5-minute prediction-market snapshots.
\fBdaemon collectors status\fR reports whether
those jobs are present, enabled, failed, or stale; \fBdaemon collectors run\fR
runs them once immediately.
.TP
.B coverage [QUERY] [--gaps]
Show CLI parity by app area.
.SH MARKET AND DATA COMMANDS
.TP
.B quote SYMBOL...
Fetch market quotes.
.TP
.B crypto-latency sample [BTC-USD] [--sources coinbase,kraken,binanceus,bitcointicker] [--duration-ms N] [--min-live-sources N]
Race public crypto WebSocket trade feeds using local receive timestamps. Reports
freshest source, last-tick ages, and cross-source spread in basis points. No API
keys are used. The bitcointicker source is parsed from its public TCP ticker
relay and should be treated as an advisory website reference, not an execution
venue.
.TP
.B crypto balance|orders|fills|ticker|book|candles|fees|readiness
Read configured crypto venue data from the CLI.
.TP
.B crypto fees [show|set|reset|tiers] [--venue VENUE]
Show or update the local fee profile used by crypto order previews. Use
\fBcrypto fees tiers\fR to print the Coinbase Advanced maker/taker tier table.
Settings include maker/taker basis points, rebate percent, optional free-fee
allowance handling, and slippage basis points. Mutating commands require \fB--yes\fR.
.TP
.B crypto readiness [SYMBOL]
Check exchange daemon readiness, quote/order-book reads, balance reads, live
trading gates, allowed venue, and fee profile.
.TP
.B crypto buy|sell SYMBOL QUANTITY [--type market|limit] [--limit-price PRICE] [--post-only] [--yes]
Preview a crypto order by default, including estimated fee, spread, slippage
buffer, and round-trip breakeven. Add \fB--yes\fR to submit through the existing
guarded crypto order path. \fBcrypto cancel ORDER_ID SYMBOL --yes\fR cancels an
open order.
.TP
.B news latest|search|monitors
Read and manage market news.
.TP
.B research quote|company|financials|filings|insiders|13f|politicians|health|sources
Run equity research, ownership-data, and research-source health queries.
.TP
.B macro fred|bls|calendar|cb|ons|statcan|census|dbnomics|gov
Fetch macroeconomic and government data.
.TP
.B data connectors|connections|stats
Manage local data-source connections.
.TP
.B data lake status|ensure|manifest|path|mirror-edge|mirror-decisions|mirror-broker-events|kalshi|decisions|broker-events|query
Manage the profile-local research lake. The lake writes JSONL datasets under
\fBdata/lake\fR and uses the local \fBduckdb\fR executable for fast SQL over
raw ticks, market snapshots, model outputs, decisions, broker events, and
research records. \fBdata lake mirror-edge --symbol BTC\fR mirrors recent edge
ticks/model outputs; \fBdata lake mirror-decisions\fR and
\fBdata lake mirror-broker-events\fR backfill edge decisions and broker/order
audit events; \fBdata lake kalshi --family crypto\fR lists captured Kalshi
market snapshots; \fBdata lake decisions\fR and \fBdata lake broker-events\fR
show the signal -> decision -> order trail; \fBdata lake query --sql "select count(*) from raw_ticks"\fR
runs local DuckDB SQL.
.TP
.B files list|search|read|write|import|download|delete
Manage File Manager artifacts.
.TP
.B notes list|search|show|create|update|export
Manage local research notes.
.TP
.B notebook list|show|path|seed|open|create|run
Manage the bundled notebook catalog, local working copies, and code-cell runs.
.TP
.B report state|add|bulk|save|load
Build and manage Report Builder documents.
.TP
.B excel read|write|append|clear
Read and mutate local CSV/XLSX files. Google Sheets helpers are available as
\fBexcel google-read\fR, \fBgoogle-write\fR, \fBgoogle-append\fR, and
\fBgoogle-clear\fR.
.TP
.B workspace layouts|show|export|import|template|panels|open
Manage saved layouts and visible GUI panels.
.SH TRADING AND PORTFOLIO COMMANDS
.TP
.B watchlist list|show|create|add|remove|lookup
Manage local watchlists.
.TP
.B portfolio list|show|create|add|sell|tx
Manage local portfolios.
.TP
.B edge evaluate|microstructure|scalp-gate|spot-swing-gate|crypto-recommend|crypto-universe|decision-cockpit|context|kalshi-scan|research|snapshot-kalshi|journal-kalshi-scan|impulse|btc5m|btc5m-live|crypto-hourly|crypto-hourly-live|observe|train|model|probability|gate|journal|journal-evaluate-btc5m-live|backfill|collect|cockpit|selftest-leakage|add|list|show|update|close|remove
Score and persist local stock, Kalshi, and Polymarket edge ideas. Compares
market probability to user/model probability after spread, fees, liquidity,
and confidence. Mutating commands require
.B --yes
and data stays in the active local profile.
.PP
.B edge kalshi-scan
fetches public live Kalshi markets, classifies each market family, and shows
the research drivers/data sources needed before a trade can clear the gate, e.g.
\fBedge kalshi-scan --limit 100 --family macro\fR.
.PP
.B edge research
fetches one Kalshi ticker, prints its classification, data-source checklist,
cost/liquidity gate, and optional edge score if an independent model
probability is supplied, e.g.
\fBedge research KX... --model-prob 62 --confidence 70\fR.
.PP
.B edge impulse
samples public crypto feeds, computes rolling 5s/15s/60s BTC movement,
velocity, confidence, and a no-trade gate, e.g.
\fBedge impulse BTC-USD --window 15s --sources coinbase,bitcointicker\fR.
.PP
.B edge crypto-recommend
samples live crypto microstructure for one symbol, applies local fee/spread/
slippage gates, and journals a buy/watch/no-buy recommendation without placing
an order, e.g.
\fBedge crypto-recommend BTC/USD --venue coinbase --horizon-sec 60\fR.
.PP
.B edge spot-swing-gate
is the longer-horizon companion to scalp-gate. It scans major spot crypto for
1h/4h/1d move candidates, uses round-trip fees plus slippage, safety, and a
minimum profit hurdle, then journals buy/watch/no-buy decisions into the same
spot lane, e.g. \fBedge spot-swing-gate --horizon 1h --venue coinbase_tier2\fR.
.PP
.B edge scalp-gate
is a stricter scalping/day-trading pre-trade gate. It samples live crypto tape,
estimates round-trip breakeven from fee, spread, slippage, and a safety buffer,
requires local proof/trust history unless warmup is explicitly allowed, and never
places an order. Add \fB--watch --iterations N --interval-sec N\fR to run a
paper observation session, e.g.
\fBedge scalp-gate BTC-USD --watch --iterations 20 --allow-warmup\fR.
\fBdaemon collectors repair\fR also installs short-horizon scalp-gate jobs and
15-second proof/trust scorecards so the daemon can keep evidence warm locally.
.PP
\fBdaemon scalp venues --maker\fR compares maker-mode fee floors by venue before
you choose what to paper-test.
\fBdaemon scalp start BTC-USD --cadence-ms 250 --amounts 25,50 --venue coinbase_tier2 --liquidity maker --min-profit-bps 10 --paper\fR enables the persistent
paper-only millisecond microstructure engine inside the daemon. It keeps local
crypto feeds open, writes a millisecond tick tape, scores 250ms/500ms/1s/5s
features, and stores paper decisions for inspection with \fBdaemon scalp status\fR
and \fBdaemon scalp tape --decisions\fR. Supported cost profiles include
\fBcoinbase_advanced\fR base tier, \fBcoinbase_tier2\fR...\fBcoinbase_tier9\fR,
\fBkraken_pro\fR, \fBbinanceus\fR, and \fBalpaca_crypto\fR. \fBbitcointicker\fR is used only for BTC.
.PP
.B edge crypto-universe
runs the same local recommendation path across a crypto universe, keeps each
symbol separate, and adds a BTC-anchor/breadth summary for context, e.g.
\fBedge crypto-universe --symbols BTC,ETH,SOL --venue coinbase --horizon-sec 60\fR.
.PP
.B edge decision-cockpit
shows crypto spot and prediction-market lanes side by side so a spot NO BUY is
not confused with a Kalshi or BTC 5-minute prediction-market decision, e.g.
\fBedge decision-cockpit --symbols BTC,ETH,SOL\fR.
.PP
.B edge context
inventories local public/legal evidence for a symbol: cached news, decision
journal rows, model output snapshots, broker audit rows, and the follow-up
research commands for SEC insiders, 13F holders, politician disclosures, filings,
or crypto microstructure, e.g. \fBedge context AAPL --asset-class equity\fR.
.PP
.B edge journal crypto-stats
prints the post-cost crypto recommendation scorecard by symbol and horizon:
BUY wins only when the later move beats fee, spread, and slippage; NO BUY wins
when the move was not good enough after cost.
.PP
.B edge journal evidence|paper-sim|proof-loop|trust|regimes|no-trade|rare-alerts|replay
turns the crypto recommendation journal into an audit and learning loop:
\fBevidence\fR explains a decision from stored features only,
\fBpaper-sim\fR simulates fixed-size BUY candidates after cost,
\fBproof-loop\fR joins signal decisions, matching broker audit events, and matured post-cost results,
\fBtrust\fR ranks symbols by resolved post-cost performance,
\fBregimes\fR buckets accuracy by trend/chop/conflict/spread/thin-data states,
\fBno-trade\fR shows why the system is standing down,
\fBrare-alerts\fR finds fresh high-edge BUY candidates, and
\fBreplay\fR walks historical recommendations in timestamp order.
.PP
.B edge btc5m
scores a BTC five-minute prediction-market idea as a directional buy-only
dry run. It combines BTC impulse, entry window, market probability, spread,
liquidity, and safety buffer; it does not place orders, e.g.
\fBedge btc5m --market-prob 52 --direction up --seconds-left 120\fR.
.PP
.B edge btc5m-live
fetches the current public Polymarket BTC five-minute Up/Down event, samples
fresh BTC ticks, and returns a dry-run edge/no-trade decision, e.g.
\fBedge btc5m-live --duration-ms 65000 --window 60s --min-move-usd 70\fR.
.PP
.B edge crypto-hourly
uses BTC as a short-horizon anchor for hourly crypto prediction contracts and
rejects signals that fail the net-edge, anchor-move, liquidity, cost, or safety
buffer gate, e.g.
\fBedge crypto-hourly --btc-prob 57 --market ETH=50 --market SOL=48 --min-edge 5 --safety-buffer 1\fR.
.PP
.B edge crypto-hourly-live
derives the BTC anchor from fresh public exchange ticks, then applies the same
gate to supplied hourly crypto market probabilities, e.g.
\fBedge crypto-hourly-live --market ETH=50 --market SOL=48 --duration-ms 16000\fR.
.PP
.B edge observe
records a local training observation for an independent probability model.
Horizons are \fB5m\fR, \fB15m\fR, \fB1h\fR, and \fBdaily\fR. Outcomes may be
added immediately or later, e.g.
\fBedge observe --horizon 15m --market-prob 49 --btc-prob 56 --move-15s 0.08 --outcome win\fR.
.PP
.B edge train
fits local transparent model weights per symbol and horizon from settled
observations, e.g. \fBedge train --horizon all --symbol BTC --min-samples 30\fR.
.PP
.B edge model
prints model readiness, sample count, base rate, and calibration score for
each horizon, e.g. \fBedge model --symbol BTC\fR.
.PP
.B edge probability
estimates an independent local probability for \fB5m\fR, \fB15m\fR, \fB1h\fR,
or \fBdaily\fR using the trained model when ready and a conservative heuristic
fallback while collecting, e.g.
\fBedge probability --horizon 1h --market-prob 53 --btc-prob 58 --move-60s 0.12\fR.
Use \fB--publish\fR to write a timestamped model-output snapshot that other
horizons may consume later without lookahead.
.PP
.B edge gate
runs the meta decision layer from timestamp-safe model outputs and prints
TRADE CANDIDATE, WATCH, NO TRADE, BAD PRICE, TOO LATE, or NOT ENOUGH DATA, e.g.
\fBedge gate --horizon 5m --market-prob 49 --btc-prob 56 --move-15s 0.10\fR.
.PP
.B edge backfill
downloads public one-minute crypto candles into the local profile database,
persists close ticks, derives settled observations for 5m, 15m, 1h, and daily
horizons, and can train models after import. Coinbase is the default public
source; Binance is also supported where available, e.g.
\fBedge backfill --source coinbase --symbol BTC --days 30 --train\fR.
.PP
.B edge collect
samples public live crypto prices and stores raw ticks in the active local
profile database, e.g.
\fBedge collect BTC --sources coinbase,kraken,bitcointicker --watch --interval-ms 1000\fR.
Coinbase and Kraken are exchange references; Bitcointicker is treated as an
advisory/lag comparison feed.
.PP
.B edge cockpit
prints an organized terminal cockpit for the selected symbol and horizon:
local profile, data/model readiness, horizon model table, probability signals,
primary meta-gate decision, and useful next commands. It can also bootstrap
missing data and train before rendering, e.g.
\fBedge cockpit --symbol BTC --horizon 15m --market-prob 50 --backfill-if-needed --train --days 30\fR.
Use \fB--watch --interval-sec 5\fR to keep the terminal open and redraw the
cockpit until interrupted. Add \fB--collect\fR to sample fresh public ticks on
each redraw.
.PP
.B edge selftest-leakage
inserts a past and future test model output, then proves the feature builder
uses only outputs at or before the decision timestamp.
.TP
.B playlist templates|list|show|follow|unfollow|status|run
Strategy playlists combine a goal, risk profile, watched assets, CLI run
command, daemon monitor, AI explanation role, and broker-execution boundary.
For example, \fBplaylist follow btc-hourly-edge --every-sec 60 --yes\fR stores
the playlist under the selected local profile and creates its daemon monitor
job. Live trading remains gated; playlists monitor, explain, paper-run, or
prepare candidates until a separate guarded broker or prediction order flow
submits.
.TP
.B strategy list|templates|show|backtest|paper-run|deploy
Manage saved trading strategies, run native backtests, route into strategy
playlists, and open guarded deploy.
.TP
.B trade accounts|drafts|prepare|submit|paper|live|fast
Manage guarded order workflows. Mutating or live commands require explicit
safety flags and local gates.
.TP
.B scanner list|add|events
Manage persisted scanner alert watches.
.TP
.B notify providers|set|send|test
Configure and send local notifications.
.SH AI COMMANDS
.TP
.B ask PROMPT...
Run a headless LLM request with OpenTerminal tools.
.TP
.B ai providers|use|test
Inspect and configure local AI provider settings.
.TP
.B ai recipes
List bundled AI analysis playbooks.
.TP
.B ai recipe show NAME
Print a bundled playbook.
.TP
.B ai recipe run NAME TARGET...
Ask the configured model to run a bundled playbook.
.TP
.B brief|risk|thesis|radar TARGET
Shortcut AI workflows for common analysis recipes.
.SH APP CONTROL COMMANDS
.TP
.B screens [QUERY]
List openable app screens.
.TP
.B open SCREEN
Open a screen in the focused GUI window.
.TP
.B actions [QUERY]
List registered app actions.
.TP
.B action ID [KEY=VALUE...]
Invoke a registered app action.
.TP
.B mcp list|search|describe|call
Inspect and call OpenTerminal tools directly.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
openterminalcli --headless quote AAPL BTC-USD
openterminalcli --headless doctor
openterminalcli --headless doctor --live-ai
openterminalcli --headless security network-audit
openterminalcli --headless security network-audit --no-sockets
openterminalcli --headless setup
openterminalcli --headless setup profile name="Ada Lovelace" nickname=ada
printf '%s' "$OPENAI_API_KEY" | openterminalcli --headless setup ai openai --api-key-stdin
openterminalcli --headless crypto balance
openterminalcli --headless crypto fees
openterminalcli --headless crypto readiness BTC/USD
openterminalcli --headless crypto book BTC/USD --limit 5
openterminalcli --headless crypto buy BTC/USD 0.0001 --limit-price 62000 --post-only
openterminalcli --headless macro fred UNRATE
openterminalcli --headless excel read ./model.xlsx --range A1:D20
openterminalcli --headless workspace layouts --recent
openterminalcli --headless ai recipes
openterminalcli ai recipe run comps NVDA
openterminalcli open profile
.EE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I src/cli/README.md
Detailed CLI usage notes.
.TP
.I packaging/cli/completions/
Shell completion scripts.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 2
Usage or validation error.
.TP
.B 3
No GUI/daemon is attached in attach mode.
.TP
.B 5
Tool or command failure.
.TP
.B 6
Transport timeout or unavailable service.
.SH SEE ALSO
